<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/93000928/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """In accordance with the "Normativa de Evaluación del Aprendizaje de la Universidad Politécnica de Madrid, 26/05/2022", all the students will be evaluated using the same method, which should be progressive by default. Evaluation will assess if students have acquired all the competences of the subject. Thus, evaluation through extraordinary assessment will be carried out considering all the evaluation techniques used in progressive and global evaluation.
Evaluation activities that assess learning outcomes that cannot be recovered outside the teaching period are mandatory; these activities will be clearly described and justified in this learning guide.
The evaluation of this subject involves:
PROGRESSIVE EVALUATION (100 %)
The student will be evaluated for each session with his work done during the laboratory session and the homework. The final mark will be the average of the marks of the 8 laboratory sessions. The practical sessions will be performed in groups if the number of students enrolled in the subject is high enough.
Non-recoverable compulsory activities (50%): Practical Sessions 3, 4, 5 and 8, and their related activities. These sessions cannot be performed outside the teaching period. The practical sessions 4 and 5 (related with antennas measurements) must be carried out in the anechoic chamber, which is a UPM facility involved in research and other activities during the year. Practical sessions 3 (Active Components Characterization with complex wave forms) and 8 (material characterization in free space), involve the use of research instrumentation, which also exhibit a limited time to use for teaching activities,
GLOBAL EVALUATION (100 %)
The global evaluation consists on delivery the reports of all the practical sessions and answering questions about them. This activity will take place in the day defined by Junta de Escuela in the exam period. Students who have not completed some of the recoverable practical sessions (1,2, 6 and 7) during the teaching period may additionally recover one of them outside this period with the presence of a professor. This session will be selected by the professors in accordance with their availability and the available teaching labs. The grades of the non-recoverable sessions (50%) will contribute to the final mark of the ordinary assessment just in case the students have performed the practical session during the teaching period.
EXTRAORDINARY ASSESSMENT (100 %)
The extraordinary evaluation will be carried out using the global evaluation described above."""@es ;
